Super Eagles captain Ahmed Musa said    the on-going Africa Cup of Nations  Cameroon 2021 would be his last but remain hopeful  of participating at  the 2022 World Cup in Qatar The former Leicester City man has been a regular for the Super Eagles since his debut in September 2010. The 29-year-old has featured in two World Cups, and he is currently Nigeria’s highest goal scorer in the competition.   Nigeria faces testy tie against Egypt in AFCON     Eguavoen: Eagles’ win greater than personal glory     Eagles ‘ll tame Salah,  says Simon   Also, this Nations Cup would be his third. Musa was part of the late Stephen Keshi’s team that claimed gold in 2013 and was also part of the team that finished in third place in 2019. This edition will be his first as captain of the Super Eagles  as well as his finale as he claimed. - Advertisement - “I didn’t say I will retire from international football after this AFCON, but this will be my last AFCON, and we still have the World Cup that I will go,” Musa said in the pre-match conference for Nigeria’s first game.